  "title": "Your guide to user-generated content",
  "link": "https://blog.google/products/adsense/your-guide-user-generated-content/",
  "description": "<html><head></head><body><div class=\"block-paragraph\"><div class=\"rich-text\"><p>User comments are a great way to drive discussion and engagement around articles. But if a publisher wants to run ads on pages where user comments appear, all of the content on those pages — including comments — must follow our <a href=\"https://support.google.com/adsense/answer/10502938\">Publisher Policies</a>. Publishers are responsible for ensuring that comment sections, forums, social media postings or anything else that users generate on their site or app are compliant with our <a href=\"https://support.google.com/adsense/answer/48182\">Program Policies</a>. This content is also subject to our <a href=\"https://support.google.com/adsense/answer/9335567\">Publisher Restrictions</a>.</p><p>To help publishers manage user-generated content (UGC), we’re sharing a new <a href=\"https://services.google.com/fh/files/blogs/user_generated_content_infographic.pdf\">infographic</a> and <a href=\"https://support.google.com/adsense/troubleshooter/11418986\">troubleshooter</a> with important information, like what to consider before incorporating UGC and helpful management strategies.<br/><br/>Check out the infographic below, and <a href=\"https://services.google.com/fh/files/blogs/user_generated_content_infographic.pdf\"><b>download or bookmark it</b></a> for easy reference.</p></div></div><div class=\"block-image_full_width\"><div class=\"h-c-page\"><div class=\"article-image h-c-grid__col--10 h-c-grid__col--offset-1 h-c-grid__col-l--offset-2 h-c-grid__col-l--8\"><a class=\"article-image--link\"><img alt=\"This is an image of the first section of the infographic. There is a decision tree if there will be a user generated content or not. Exact same information that is in this image can be found via downloading the infographic.\" class=\"article-image--full\" data-loading='{\n                \"mobile\": \"https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/user_generated_content_infographic_part_1.max-500x500.jpg\",\n                \"desktop\": \"https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/user_generated_content_infographic_part_1.max-1000x1000.jpg\"\n              }' loading=\"lazy\" src=\" https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/user_generated_content_infographic_part_1.max-100x100.jpg \" tabindex=\"0\"/></a></div></div></div><div class=\"block-image_full_width\"><div class=\"h-c-page\"><div class=\"article-image h-c-grid__col--10 h-c-grid__col--offset-1 h-c-grid__col-l--offset-2 h-c-grid__col-l--8\"><a class=\"article-image--link\"><img alt=\"second part of the infographic with 6 blue and white bullets explaining how a publisher can monitor the user generated content to stay policy compliant At the bottom there are 4 different resources given\" class=\"article-image--full\" data-loading='{\n                \"mobile\": \"https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/user_generated_content_infographic_part_2.max-500x500.jpg\",\n                \"desktop\": \"https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/user_generated_content_infographic_part_2.max-1000x1000.jpg\"\n              }' loading=\"lazy\" src=\" https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-uniblog-publish-prod/images/user_generated_content_infographic_part_2.max-100x100.jpg \" tabindex=\"0\"/></a></div></div></div></body></html>",
